### 2. Find the actual root cause(s)
Do not make shallow guesses.

Investigate likely failure points such as:
- listeners only attached for one event type
- listeners attached to wrong execution context
- service worker sleeping or losing state
- message passing failures between content script and background
- side panel not subscribing to updates after first render
- React/Vue/state bug causing UI not to re-render after first event
- stale closure / overwritten state array
- event deduplication logic dropping valid events
- storage writes replacing the full array instead of appending
- race conditions between activeTab changes and content script listeners
- manifest permission issues
- host permission gaps
- content script not injected on newly navigated pages
- tab change events captured but DOM interaction events never attached
- recording flag not consistently shared across components
- stop/start logic breaking subsequent event listeners
- debounce/throttle logic suppressing too much
- CSP or extension isolation issues
- event handlers bound but not cleaned/rebound correctly on navigation

Identify the root cause with evidence from the code.

